race.comment: BILLY BOOM (2) should be ready to strike after a solid return here over this trip. Trial win since keeps him ticking over and Wiggins sticking is a strong lead. Looks well placed to break through. HIT (5) was narrowly denied here first-up before failing to fire on the synthetic. Back to this track and trip suits and he's capable of bouncing back hard. BRILLIANT EIGHT (7) has returned in good order, following his maiden win with a brave second at Gympie. Has the pace to be prominent and is a genuine contender. RIVA D'AMOR (10) resumes for the Hansen yard and has test figures that measure up. Don't dismiss. IRISH THUNDER (8) is hard to catch but has form at the trip to sneak into the finish at odds.
